46 "48-14-4.
47 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'department' means the Department of Natural
48 Resources.
49 (b) Each county in which is located 20,000 acres or more of unimproved real property
50 belonging to the state and under the custody or control of the department, in which such
51 state owned property exceeds 10 percent of the taxable real property in the county, and in
52 which such property represents 10 percent or more of the assessed tax digest of the county
53 may receive from the department an annual grant as provided in this Code section.
54 (c) For each county eligible to receive a grant pursuant to subsection (b) of this Code
55 section, the department shall calculate the approximate value of public services which the
56 county provides the department each year; provided, however, that such sum shall not
57 exceed the amount the county would charge any other landowner for such services. The
58 department shall request funds in its annual operating budget each year to reimburse all
59 eligible counties for the provision of such services. In the event the amount appropriated
60 in any year is less than the amount requested, each eligible county shall receive a pro rata
61 share based on the estimated value of services provided.
62 (d) The department is directed to make an annual calculation of the amount of unimproved
63 state owned real property under its custody or control and determine which counties are
64 eligible for a grant pursuant to subsection (b) of this Code section. The first such
65 determination shall be completed not later than December 31, 1993, and each subsequent
66 determination shall be made not later than December 31 of each year. The department is
67 further directed to calculate the approximate value of public services provided by each
68 eligible county as provided in subsection (c) of this Code section.
